-{"id":"franken_networkx-f6vn","title":"parity: Graph, DiGraph, and MultiGraph edges() should accept nbunch with data/default keywords","description":"Graph, DiGraph, and MultiGraph currently mis-handle NetworkX's edges(nbunch, data=..., default=...) call form. For example, edges(['a'], data='missing', default='NA') raises a TypeError in FrankenNetworkX, while upstream NetworkX returns the filtered edge tuples with the requested default value. Match the upstream keyword-dispatch contract for edges() on these graph classes.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:03:10.846294314Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:03:10.846294314Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
