 {"id":"franken_networkx-f6yv","title":"parity: conversion live views NodeView should support set algebra","description":"The top-level to_directed(...) and to_undirected(...) live views currently expose node views that are not set-like. In FrankenNetworkX, expressions such as view.nodes | {'z'}, view.nodes & {'a'}, and related set operations raise TypeError on both simple and multigraph conversions, while upstream NetworkX returns the expected node sets. Match the upstream NodeView set-algebra contract on conversion live views.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T10:51:44.179434824Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T10:51:44.179434824Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
